her%20is%20often%20considered%20the%20most%20important%20defensive%20player%2C%20and%20as%20such%20is%20situated%20at%20the%20right%20end%20of%20the%20defensive%20spectrum.%20There%20are%20many%20different%20types%20of%20pitchers%2C%20such%20as%20the%20starting%20pitcher%2C%20relief%20pitcher%2C%20middle%20reliever%2C%20lefty%20specialist%2C%20setup%20man%2C%20and%20closer.%3C%5C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20the%20pitcher%20also%20bats.%20Starting%20in%201973%20with%20the%20American%20League%20and%20spreading%20to%20further%20leagues%20throughout%20the%201980s%20and%201990s%2C%20the%20hitting%20duties%20of%20the%20pitcher%20have%20generally%20been%20given%20over%20to%20the%20position%20of%20designated%20hitter%2C%20a%20cause%20of%20some%20controversy.%20The%20National%20League%20in%20Major%20League%20Baseball%20and%20the%20Japanese%20Central%20League%20are%20among%20the%20remaining%20leagues%20that%20have%20not%20adopted%20the%20designated%20hitter%20position.%3C%5C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E1.%20Overview%3C%5C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20most%20cases%2C%20the%20objective%20of%20the%20pitcher%20is%20to%20deliver%20the%20pitch%20to%20the%20catcher%20without%20allowing%20the%20batter%20to%20hit%20the%20ball%20with%20the%20bat.%20A%20successful%20pitch%20is%20delivered%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20the%20batter%20either%20allows%20the%20pitch%20to%20pass%20through%20the%20strike%20zone%2C%20swings%20the%20bat%20at%20the%20ball%20and%20misses%20it%2C%20or%20hits%20the%20ball%20poorly%20%28resulting%20in%20a%20pop%20fly%20or%20ground%20out%29.%20If%20the%20batter%20elects%20not%20to%20swing%20at%20the%20pitch%2C%20it%20is%20called%20a%20strike%20if%20any%20part%20of%20the%20ball%20passes%20through%20the%20strike%20zone%20and%20a%20ball%20when%20no%20part%20of%20the%20ball%20passes%20through%20the%20strike%20zone.%5Cu00a0%3C%5C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%5Bcaption%20id%3D%5C%22attachment_751%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22alignnone%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22730%5C%22%5D%3Cimg%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-751%